summary.name: Flights Dataset
summary.dataset_description: A dataset containing information about 200,000 flights, including delay, distance, time, distance range, and delay range.

fields.description: The delay time of the flight in minutes.
The distance of the flight in miles.
The duration of the flight in hours.
The range of distance the flight falls into, represented as an interval.
The range of delay time the flight falls into, represented as a string.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flight delays?
goals.rationale: This tells us how many flights experienced delays and the range of delay times.

goals.question: How does distance affect flight time?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of distance vs time
goals.rationale: This helps us understand the relationship between distance and time, and if there are any outliers or patterns.

goals.question: What is the average delay time for each distance range?
goals.visualization: bar chart of delay vs distance range
goals.rationale: This helps us identify if there are any distance ranges that experience more delays than others.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flight distances?
goals.rationale: This tells us how many flights were short-haul vs long-haul, and the range of distances.

goals.question: Which delay range is the most common?
goals.rationale: This helps us understand the proportion of flights that experience different levels of delay.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', bins=50, kde=True, color='blue')
    median_delay = data['delay'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_delay, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median Delay: {median_delay:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='distance', y='time', data=data)
    plt.title('How does distance affect flight time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    plt.ylabel('Time (hours)')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    avg_delay_by_distance_range = data.groupby('distance_range')['delay'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='distance_range', y='delay', data=avg_delay_by_distance_range)
    plt.title('What is the average delay time for each distance range?', wrap=True)
    chart.set(xlabel='Distance Range', ylabel='Average Delay (minutes)')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    delay_counts = data['delay_range'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(delay_counts, labels=delay_counts.index, autopct='%.2f%%')
    plt.title('Which delay range is the most common?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Delay Ranges', loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
